'''the fox in the henhouse:''' a metaphor used to describe relationships wherein a predator is granted free reign within the prey's home confinement, often used in the political sense.

In 2006 [http://www.thefoxinthehenhouse.com/] became newsworthy after U.S. populist-progressive radio talk show host Jim Hightower ([http://jimhightower.com/]) began making refence to the site promoting the book ''The Fox in the Henhouse: How Privatization Threatens Democracy,'' which posits that the United States' public sector (assets and services) is being systematically and perhaps irreversibly commandeered by corporations, particularly under the administration of [[George W. Bush]].
